The four remaining winners of the Brown Sticker Competition finally entered the factory, where they were greeted by the sterile chaos of a modern mega-corporation. While it appeared to be a well-oiled machine, Wankoff led them to a room that was suffering from a peculiar plague of mismanagement or non-management. The Chocolate Swamp. The room was supposed to be where all the chocolate is made, but no chocolate has been made in years since the swamp and the poop from the sewer system and toilet manufacturing part of the factory has infiltrated the chocolate swamp, making it a confusing, smelly mess. A babble-like tower made of chocolate and sludge lingered in the distance of the swamp, and so Wankov suggested they head in that direction on his speedboat, attended by one of the frog workers, known as Sullivans. The Sullivans sang their song about how they are slaves, and lamented to Wankoff about how they built the tower to protect themselves from the swamp monster that has been terrorizing them for years. The swamp monster then made an appearance, and after Waylon Au Revoir cleverly appealed to his better nature by feeding him treats, the gang spotted a tube sticking out of the swamp monster's backside that was pumping it full of shit, making it big and angry. Our heroes acted quickly, defeating the two, though not without some serious casualties. Weyland suffering the most damage, and nor without Pinocchio discovering that when he tells jokes, his nose grows in diameter, turning him into some kind of horrifying freak with essentially a tree trunk on his face.
